.TH "gsm_data_alloc" 9 "gsm_data_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gsm_data_alloc \- allocate data frame
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct gsm_msg *" gsm_data_alloc
.BI "(struct gsm_mux *gsm "  ","
.BI "u8 addr "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "u8 ctrl "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gsm" 12
GSM mux
.IP "addr" 12
DLCI address
.IP "len" 12
length excluding header and FCS
.IP "ctrl" 12
control byte

Allocate a new data buffer for sending frames with data. Space is left
at the front for header bytes but that is treated as an implementation
detail and not for the high level code to use
